<note id="notfhsst_id1000" type="tip">There is no space and no dot between the prefix and the symbol for the unit.</note>
      <para id="id66297">Here are some examples of the use of prefixes:</para>
      <list id="id66300" display="block" list-type="bulleted">
        <item id="uid33">40000 m can be written as 40 km (kilometre)
</item>
        <item id="uid34">0,001 g is the same as <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> g and can be written as 1 mg (milligram)
</item>
        <item id="uid35"><m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> N can be written as 2,5 MN (meganewton)
</item>
        <item id="uid36">250000 A can be written as 250 kA (kiloampere) or 0,250 MA (megaampere)
</item>
        <item id="uid37">0,000000075 s can be written as 75 ns (nanoseconds)
</item>
        <item id="uid38"><m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>7</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> mol can be rewritten as <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mn>10</m:mn><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math> mol, which is the same as 0,3 <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>μ</m:mi></m:math>mol (micromol)
</item>
      </list>
